commit.message: LICENSE: Update copyright year
expr: Help gcc see that variables aren't used uninitialized

Use 'bool' in headers instead of '_Bool'

_Bool is deprecated in C23, and using it breaks bootstrap with
implementations that don't fully support C99 and define bool to
some other type in stdbool.h.
map: Use simpler fnv-1a hash function
Use C23 keywords in test data

decl: Check alignment range

We store alignment as int, so check that it fits to avoid
implementation-defined behavior.

Also, fix printf format specifier and drop unneeded parentheses.
